---
title: Typerblam
bpm: 120
visualiser:
  count: 16
elements: 
  - Sample 
---

{% extends 'layouts/example.njk' %}

{% block visual %}
<style>
  #glyphs {
    transform: scale(max(0.25, var(--stretch-x)), max(0.25, var(--stretch-y)));
  }

  @keyframes jolt {
    0% {
      transform: translateY(0);
    }
    20% {
      transform: translateY(-0.75rem);
    }
    40% {
      transform: translateY(0.5rem);
    }
    60% {
      transform: translateY(-0.25rem);
    }
    80% {
      transform: translateY(0.125rem);
    }
    100% {
      transform: translateY(0rem);
    }
  }

  #glyphs > div {
    line-height: 0;
    font-size: 100cqmin;
    animation: jolt 0.15s linear 1;
    animation-fill-mode: forwards;
    font-family: Georgia, serif;
  }
</style>
<div id="glyphs" role="img" aria-label="Animation that shows letters spelling out HyperBlam when typing sound is audible" from="#keys" class="l-screen" cycle>
  <div hidden>H</div>
  <div hidden>Y</div>
  <div hidden>P</div>
  <div hidden>E</div>
  <div hidden>R</div>
  <div hidden>B</div>
  <div hidden>L</div>
  <div hidden>A</div>
  <div hidden>M</div>
</div>
{% endblock %}

{% block audio %}
<chain-blam id="bus">
  <analyser-blam gain="100"></analyser-blam>
</chain-blam>
<pads-blam id="keys" out="bus" choke>
  <bank-blam>
    <sample-blam src="{{site.basedir}}/static/sounds/effects/key-01.mp3"></sample-blam>
    <sample-blam src="{{site.basedir}}/static/sounds/effects/key-02.mp3"></sample-blam>
    <sample-blam src="{{site.basedir}}/static/sounds/effects/key-03.mp3"></sample-blam>
    <sample-blam src="{{site.basedir}}/static/sounds/effects/key-04.mp3"></sample-blam>
    <sample-blam src="{{site.basedir}}/static/sounds/effects/key-05.mp3"></sample-blam>
  </bank-blam>
  <blam-blam prop="--stretch-x" to="#glyphs" value="0~1"></blam-blam>
  <blam-blam prop="--stretch-y" to="#glyphs" value="0~1"></blam-blam>
  <one-blam prop="hidden" to="#glyphs > *" fwd revert></one-blam>
</pads-blam>
<sequencer-blam>
  <track-blam to="#keys">
    <bar-blam s="?" chance="0.3"></bar-blam>
  </track-blam>
</sequencer-blam>
{% endblock %}

{% block dialog %}

{% renderTemplate "md" %}

This simple visualization uses two event-driven elements—`<show-blam>` and `<seed-blam>`—and a little CSS animation.

As the name suggests, `<show-blam>` just... shows stuff. In this case, I'm showing the characters for the term **HYPERBLAM** in turn. So I apply the `cycle` prop. 

```html 
<show-blam from="#keys" cycle>...</show-blam>
```

The `<seed-blam>` element is simple but powerful. It adds custom properties with random values between `0` and `1`. These can be used to randomize all sorts of styles. In this case, two seeds are applied for affecting `scale`.

```css 
show-blam {
  transform: scale(max(0.25, var(--seed-stretch-1)), max(0.25, var(--seed-stretch-2)));
}
```

(Note the `max()` function, ensuring the scale—on either axis—is never smaller than `0.25`.)

Both `<show-blam>` and `<seed-blam>` respond to the `<pads-blam>`’s generic “blam” event. That is, every time a sound is played, a new character—semi-randomly stretched—appears. 

Each character’s element has a CSS animation applied that jolts/shakes the character as it appears. This acts as a visual metaphor for the rattling sound of the keys.

{% endrenderTemplate %}

{% endblock %}

{% block controls %}

<tap-blam to="sequencer-blam" prop="playStop">
  <button aria-pressed="false" class="u-round" aria-label="play">{% icon 'playStop' %}</button>
</tap-blam>
<dial-blam to="audio-blam" prop="bpm">
  <label>
  speed
  <input type="range" min="60" max="180">
  </label>
</dial-blam>

{% endblock %}